PathShape.description:
Shape of the arrow / connection path — orthogonal to  {@link  LineStyle } , which only sets the stroke pattern (solid, dotted…). Default: 'bezier'.

- `bezier`: smooth S curve, handles along the dominant axis (default);
- `simplebezier`: same idea, more subtle curvature;
- `straight`: direct segment (bypasses sandwiched labels);
- `step`: orthogonal path with right angles;
- `smoothstep`: orthogonal path with rounded angles.

On two perfectly aligned nodes (same row/column), all shapes merge into a straight line: curvature only appears in the presence of a transverse offset (different lanes, fan-out, bidirectional tracks).
